issue.title: Allow ability to assert some callback triggers an error
issue.body: Like asserting that an exception is thrown, it might be useful that a given code triggers some expected error that shouldn't be transformed into a thrown exception. Similar to `assertThrows` we could implement an `assertTriggers`. This would be a slightly more complex implementation as we would need to interact with the global error handler and ensure that our error trapping handler only operates within the confines our of our callback.

issue.title: Allow Profiles to be created using a CSV string
issue.body: Part of refactoring the `Cspray\AnnotatedContainer\Profiles` module includes removing the `CsvActiveProfilesParser`. We should provide similar functionality in a static constructor on the new `Profiles` value object.

issue.title: Fix parameter order for `assertThrows`
issue.body:
Our `assertThrows` method has transposed the normal parameter order for assert methods. Instead of:

`assertThrows(expected, actual)`

We have:

`assertThrows(actual, expected)`

We should fix this parameter order to be more aligned with other assertions.

issue.title: Add a version attribute to the XML configuration to facilitate migrating between major versions
issue.body: In 3.0 there are significant changes to the XML configuration file and schema. There isn't really anyway to determine which version of Annotated Container is suitable for. We should add an attribute `version` to the root `<annotatedContainer>` element that dictates which `major.minor` version this schema is intended for. This can be used both by humans manually checking configurations, tooling to verify your configuration file is for the version of your Annotated Container, and to provide migration tools in the future if they become necessary.
